Preparing Your Business for AI Infrastructure Investment
If you are a business leader in the United States evaluating how to build or upgrade your AI infrastructure in 2026, there are several foundational questions worth working through before committing budget.

Is your data ready? AI models are only as powerful as the data they run on. Before investing in AI platforms or tools, assess whether your data is clean, complete, and consistently structured. Many companies discover that data quality is the single biggest blocker to AI value realization.

Do you have the right governance framework? AI in enterprise settings requires clear policies around model transparency, data privacy, bias monitoring, and regulatory compliance — especially in highly regulated industries like healthcare and fintech. Building governance infrastructure early prevents costly remediation later.

Are your marketing and sales teams aligned around AI-generated insights? Technology alone does not drive growth. The companies getting the most value from AI infrastructure are the ones that have successfully integrated AI recommendations into day-to-day commercial workflows, with clear processes for acting on the insights generated.

What is your build versus buy strategy? Not every company needs to build proprietary AI infrastructure from scratch. For many B2B organizations, partnering with specialized providers — for lead generation, ABM, content syndication, or intent data — delivers faster ROI than internal development.

